recyclables.title: Pizza Boxes
recyclables.info:
Cardboard pizza delivery boxes without leftovers or liners should be recycled; but leftover crusts, cheese and other food should not. You should flatten it and place inside your blue bin in Regina.
Source: https://www.wm.com/us/en/recycle-right/recycling-101

recyclables.title: Plastic Bags
recyclables.info:
Plastic bags are not accepted as part of curbside recycling programs - they get tangled in equipment and threaten worker safety. Do your best to reuse plastic bags and DO NOT place other recyclables inside of them.
Source: https://www.wm.com/us/en/recycle-right/recycling-101

recyclables.title: Needles
recyclables.info:
Do not place needles in blue bins.
Using heavy gloves and a pair of tongs or pliers, please dispose of any needle(s) in an empty, non-breakable, hard-sided container, with a lid that needles cannot poke through (ie. pop bottle or small coffee tin). Please use the tongs to safely pick up the needle(s), place them in the container and fasten the lid. Containers can be taken to needle drop off boxes in the city.
Source: https://www.regina.ca/home-property/safety-emergencies/safe-needle-disposal/

recyclables.title: Paper
recyclables.info:
Paper can be recycled in blue bins.
If paper is soiled or wet, compost it.
Source: https://www.wm.com/us/en/recycle-right/recycling-101

recyclables.title: Plastic Bottles and Containers
recyclables.info:
All plastic bottles and containers labelled #1-7 are acceptable in blue bins, and anything not labelled #1-7 is not.
Source: https://www.regina.ca/home-property/recycling-garbage/recycling/

recyclables.title: Soup Cans
recyclables.info:
Please rinse out cans and place them inside blue bins.
Source: https://www.regina.ca/home-property/recycling-garbage/recycling/

recyclables.title: Bottle Caps
recyclables.info:
Bottle caps are not recyclable, so do not place them inside blue bins or bring them to bottle disposal centres.
Source: https://www.regina.ca/home-property/recycling-garbage/recycling/

recyclables.title: Rope
recyclables.info:
Rope is not recyclable, so do not place it inside blue bins.
Source: https://www.regina.ca/home-property/recycling-garbage/recycling/

recyclables.title: Styrofoam
recyclables.info:
Styrofoam is not recyclable in blue bins. Place it in your brown bin for disposal, or drop off at 225 6th Avenue East, Regina SK. Please call ahead.
Source: https://www.regina.ca/home-property/recycling-garbage/recycling/
